<subSubSection pageId="3" pageNumber="354" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="3.[151,1437,876,2031]" box="[199,696,1092,1117]" pageId="3" pageNumber="354">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,321,1092,1117]" pageId="3" pageNumber="354">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
With the characters of the genus.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="3.[151,1437,876,2031]" pageId="3" pageNumber="354">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,455,1127,1152]" pageId="3" pageNumber="354">Preserved coloration.</emphasis>
Unknown after 18 years in preservative. Epicranium, interantennal region, genae, and frons dark brown, fading into light yellowish pigmentation peripherally on labrum, clypeus, and genal margins (
<figureCitation box="[159,249,1199,1224]" captionStart="FIGURE 3" captionStartId="5.[151,250,1931,1953]" captionTargetBox="[210,1370,197,1907]" captionTargetId="figure@5.[207,1376,193,1911]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURE 3. Somatic featUres of Xanthotropis media n. comb. A. Head and left antenna, anterior View (right antenna missing). B. CollUm and tergites 2–3, dorsal View. C. Right paranota of rings 2–4, dorsal View; the red arrows denote the anterolateral teeth. D. Rings 17–19 and telson, dorsal View. Scale lines: 1.00 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/1439776/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="354">Fig. 3A</figureCitation>
). Antennomeres yellow, thus contrasting with dark head (
<figureCitation box="[896,1031,1199,1224]" captionStart="FIGURE 3" captionStartId="5.[151,250,1931,1953]" captionTargetBox="[210,1370,197,1907]" captionTargetId="figure@5.[207,1376,193,1911]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURE 3. Somatic featUres of Xanthotropis media n. comb. A. Head and left antenna, anterior View (right antenna missing). B. CollUm and tergites 2–3, dorsal View. C. Right paranota of rings 2–4, dorsal View; the red arrows denote the anterolateral teeth. D. Rings 17–19 and telson, dorsal View. Scale lines: 1.00 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/1439776/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="354">Figs. 3A–B</figureCitation>
). Metaterga brown, paranota yellow and becoming progressively lighter laterad; caudal margins with narrow yellow bands mediad becoming progressively thinner caudad, absent from caudal metaterga (
<figureCitation box="[847,983,1271,1296]" captionStart="FIGURE 3" captionStartId="5.[151,250,1931,1953]" captionTargetBox="[210,1370,197,1907]" captionTargetId="figure@5.[207,1376,193,1911]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURE 3. Somatic featUres of Xanthotropis media n. comb. A. Head and left antenna, anterior View (right antenna missing). B. CollUm and tergites 2–3, dorsal View. C. Right paranota of rings 2–4, dorsal View; the red arrows denote the anterolateral teeth. D. Rings 17–19 and telson, dorsal View. Scale lines: 1.00 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/1439776/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="354">Figs. 3B–D</figureCitation>
). Telson brown basally, yellow apically (
<figureCitation box="[159,249,1308,1333]" captionStart="FIGURE 3" captionStartId="5.[151,250,1931,1953]" captionTargetBox="[210,1370,197,1907]" captionTargetId="figure@5.[207,1376,193,1911]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURE 3. Somatic featUres of Xanthotropis media n. comb. A. Head and left antenna, anterior View (right antenna missing). B. CollUm and tergites 2–3, dorsal View. C. Right paranota of rings 2–4, dorsal View; the red arrows denote the anterolateral teeth. D. Rings 17–19 and telson, dorsal View. Scale lines: 1.00 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/1439776/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="354">Fig. 3D</figureCitation>
). Distal podomeres light yellow (
<figureCitation box="[623,710,1308,1333]" captionStart="FIGURE 3" captionStartId="5.[151,250,1931,1953]" captionTargetBox="[210,1370,197,1907]" captionTargetId="figure@5.[207,1376,193,1911]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURE 3. Somatic featUres of Xanthotropis media n. comb. A. Head and left antenna, anterior View (right antenna missing). B. CollUm and tergites 2–3, dorsal View. C. Right paranota of rings 2–4, dorsal View; the red arrows denote the anterolateral teeth. D. Rings 17–19 and telson, dorsal View. Scale lines: 1.00 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/1439776/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="354">Fig. 3B</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection lastPageId="7" lastPageNumber="358" pageId="3" pageNumber="354" type="materials_examined">
<paragraph blockId="3.[151,1437,876,2031]" lastBlockId="7.[151,1437,151,1259]" lastPageId="7" lastPageNumber="358" pageId="3" pageNumber="354">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,315,1343,1368]" pageId="3" pageNumber="354">
<typeStatus box="[199,310,1343,1368]" pageId="3" pageNumber="354">Holotype</typeStatus>
.
</emphasis>
Length 34.0 mm, maximum width 
<quantity box="[713,802,1344,1368]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="4.3" pageId="3" pageNumber="354" unit="mm" value="4.3">4.3 mm</quantity>
; W/L ratio 12.6%. 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[1017,1080,1343,1368]" pageId="3" pageNumber="354">Head</emphasis>
(
<figureCitation box="[1096,1227,1343,1368]" captionStart="FIGURE 3" captionStartId="5.[151,250,1931,1953]" captionTargetBox="[210,1370,197,1907]" captionTargetId="figure@5.[207,1376,193,1911]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURE 3. Somatic featUres of Xanthotropis media n. comb. A. Head and left antenna, anterior View (right antenna missing). B. CollUm and tergites 2–3, dorsal View. C. Right paranota of rings 2–4, dorsal View; the red arrows denote the anterolateral teeth. D. Rings 17–19 and telson, dorsal View. Scale lines: 1.00 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/1439776/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="354">Figs. 3A–B</figureCitation>
) generally smooth and shiny, coriaceous around subovoid incisura lateralis. Epicranial suture shallow, not anteriorly bifid. Interantennal isthmus narrow, 
<quantity box="[503,596,1419,1443]" metricMagnitude="-4" metricUnit="m" metricValue="4.0" pageId="3" pageNumber="354" unit="mm" value="0.4">0.4 mm</quantity>
. Antennae extending backwards to around midlength of 2nd metatergite. Antennal setae sparse except on subglobose 1 
<taxonomicName box="[673,840,1453,1481]" pageId="3" pageNumber="354" rank="subSpecies" subSpecies="antennomere">st antennomere</taxonomicName>
, 2–5 clavate, 6 longer and cylindrical, 7th short and truncate, with four apical sensory cones arranged in diads, antennomere margin invaginated between latter. Antennomere lengths (1–7, in mm): 0.4, 0.9. 0.9, 0.9, 0.9, 0.8, 0.3. Facial setae as follows: epicranial and interantennal absent, frontal 2–2, clypeal 6–6, labral about 5–5, merging with clypeal series and continuing for short distances along genal margins. 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[570,646,1601,1626]" pageId="3" pageNumber="354">Trunk</emphasis>
(
<figureCitation box="[662,797,1601,1626]" captionStart="FIGURE 3" captionStartId="5.[151,250,1931,1953]" captionTargetBox="[210,1370,197,1907]" captionTargetId="figure@5.[207,1376,193,1911]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURE 3. Somatic featUres of Xanthotropis media n. comb. A. Head and left antenna, anterior View (right antenna missing). B. CollUm and tergites 2–3, dorsal View. C. Right paranota of rings 2–4, dorsal View; the red arrows denote the anterolateral teeth. D. Rings 17–19 and telson, dorsal View. Scale lines: 1.00 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/1439776/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="354">Figs. 3B–D</figureCitation>
). Pro- and metaterga glabrous and glossy, former lightly coriaceous laterad, latter with inconspicuous microgranulations. Collum length (mm) 1.4, width 4.1; surface lightly coriaceous along anterior and caudal margins, with horizontal semilunar depression mediad, caudolateral margins sublinear, rounded anteriad, lightly coriaceous laterad (
<figureCitation box="[779,868,1709,1734]" captionStart="FIGURE 3" captionStartId="5.[151,250,1931,1953]" captionTargetBox="[210,1370,197,1907]" captionTargetId="figure@5.[207,1376,193,1911]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURE 3. Somatic featUres of Xanthotropis media n. comb. A. Head and left antenna, anterior View (right antenna missing). B. CollUm and tergites 2–3, dorsal View. C. Right paranota of rings 2–4, dorsal View; the red arrows denote the anterolateral teeth. D. Rings 17–19 and telson, dorsal View. Scale lines: 1.00 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/1439776/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="354">Fig. 3B</figureCitation>
). Paranota slanted ventrad (
<figureCitation box="[1187,1323,1709,1734]" captionStart="FIGURE 3" captionStartId="5.[151,250,1931,1953]" captionTargetBox="[210,1370,197,1907]" captionTargetId="figure@5.[207,1376,193,1911]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURE 3. Somatic featUres of Xanthotropis media n. comb. A. Head and left antenna, anterior View (right antenna missing). B. CollUm and tergites 2–3, dorsal View. C. Right paranota of rings 2–4, dorsal View; the red arrows denote the anterolateral teeth. D. Rings 17–19 and telson, dorsal View. Scale lines: 1.00 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/1439776/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="354">Figs. 3A–B</figureCitation>
); those of metaterga 2–4 with one anterolateral tooth, largest on 3rd paranota (
<figureCitation box="[898,986,1748,1773]" captionStart="FIGURE 3" captionStartId="5.[151,250,1931,1953]" captionTargetBox="[210,1370,197,1907]" captionTargetId="figure@5.[207,1376,193,1911]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURE 3. Somatic featUres of Xanthotropis media n. comb. A. Head and left antenna, anterior View (right antenna missing). B. CollUm and tergites 2–3, dorsal View. C. Right paranota of rings 2–4, dorsal View; the red arrows denote the anterolateral teeth. D. Rings 17–19 and telson, dorsal View. Scale lines: 1.00 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/1439776/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="354">Fig. 3C</figureCitation>
); caudolateral corners extending caudad beginning on 4th paranota, becoming longer and progressively more acuminate caudad. Peritremata slightly thickened, elevated above dorsal paranotal surfaces, with microgranulations on anterior and posterior margins; ozopores located caudal to midlengths on paranota 5, 7, 9, 10, 12, 13, 15–19, opening laterad. Sides of metazona smooth, generally without grooves or impressions. Pregonopodal sterna smooth and glabrous, those of rings 4, 5 with two pairs of rounded lobes, caudal margin of 6th sternum recessed to accommodate gonopodal apices when trunk compressed. Postgonopodal sterna smooth and glabrous, those of rings 8–18 with two pairs of short, rounded projections and inconspicuous bicruciform impressions. Legs generally narrow and glossy with microgranulations and short setae on all podomeres; 1 
<taxonomicName box="[551,610,151,179]" pageId="7" pageNumber="358" rank="subSpecies" subSpecies="and">st and</taxonomicName>
2nd legs short and crassate, gonapophyses short and tubular; 3rd–7th legs longer, lengths subequal. Postgonopodal legs of subequal lengths and setal tufts on tarsi; tarsal claws short, curving gently apically. Telson subtriangular, narrowly truncate and sublinear apically (
<figureCitation box="[1086,1182,226,251]" captionStart="FIGURE 3" captionStartId="5.[151,250,1931,1953]" captionTargetBox="[210,1370,197,1907]" captionTargetId="figure@5.[207,1376,193,1911]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURE 3. Somatic featUres of Xanthotropis media n. comb. A. Head and left antenna, anterior View (right antenna missing). B. CollUm and tergites 2–3, dorsal View. C. Right paranota of rings 2–4, dorsal View; the red arrows denote the anterolateral teeth. D. Rings 17–19 and telson, dorsal View. Scale lines: 1.00 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/1439776/files/figure.png" pageId="7" pageNumber="358">Fig. 3D</figureCitation>
); paraproctal margins strongly elevated with two setal pairs arranged vertically proximal to rims; hypoproct semilunar. Gonopodal aperture elliptical, approximately 
<quantity box="[539,627,299,323]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.3" pageId="7" pageNumber="358" unit="mm" value="1.3">1.3 mm</quantity>
wide and 
<quantity box="[752,840,299,323]" metricMagnitude="-4" metricUnit="m" metricValue="9.0" pageId="7" pageNumber="358" unit="mm" value="0.9">0.9 mm</quantity>
long at midpoint; anterior margin slightly concave, sides elevating progressively caudad then lowering to flat caudal margin. 
<emphasis box="[1057,1137,336,359]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="358">In situ</emphasis>
gonopodal configuration unknown; right gonopod missing and left dissected for present examination. 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[1019,1247,370,395]" pageId="7" pageNumber="358">Gonopod structure</emphasis>
(
<figureCitation box="[1263,1397,370,395]" captionStart="FIGURE 4" captionStartId="6.[151,250,1949,1971]" captionTargetBox="[207,1386,185,1934]" captionTargetId="figure@6.[200,1394,180,1936]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="FIGURE 4. Gonopodal featUres of Xanthotropis media n. comb. A. Left gonopod, lateral View. B. The same, medial View. C. The same, dorsal View. D. Right gonopod, dorsal View (modified from GoloVatch et al., 2004). Scale lines: A–C (0.5 mm), D (1000 µm)." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/1439778/files/figure.png" pageId="7" pageNumber="358">Figs. 4A–D</figureCitation>
) as follows: Coxa without apophysis, with three ventral setae equivalent in lengths to basal ones on prefemur. Latter shorter than coxa (
<figureCitation box="[363,455,442,467]" captionStart="FIGURE 4" captionStartId="6.[151,250,1949,1971]" captionTargetBox="[207,1386,185,1934]" captionTargetId="figure@6.[200,1394,180,1936]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="FIGURE 4. Gonopodal featUres of Xanthotropis media n. comb. A. Left gonopod, lateral View. B. The same, medial View. C. The same, dorsal View. D. Right gonopod, dorsal View (modified from GoloVatch et al., 2004). Scale lines: A–C (0.5 mm), D (1000 µm)." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/1439778/files/figure.png" pageId="7" pageNumber="358">Fig. 4A</figureCitation>
), demarcated from acropodite by cingulum, densely covered by setae around origin of spermatic groove, setae extending short distance along acropodite (
<figureCitation box="[963,1129,478,503]" captionStart="FIGURE 4" captionStartId="6.[151,250,1949,1971]" captionTargetBox="[207,1386,185,1934]" captionTargetId="figure@6.[200,1394,180,1936]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="FIGURE 4. Gonopodal featUres of Xanthotropis media n. comb. A. Left gonopod, lateral View. B. The same, medial View. C. The same, dorsal View. D. Right gonopod, dorsal View (modified from GoloVatch et al., 2004). Scale lines: A–C (0.5 mm), D (1000 µm)." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/1439778/files/figure.png" pageId="7" pageNumber="358">Figs. 4A; 4D</figureCitation>
). Acropodite (
<figureCitation box="[1305,1379,478,503]" captionStart="FIGURE 4" captionStartId="6.[151,250,1949,1971]" captionTargetBox="[207,1386,185,1934]" captionTargetId="figure@6.[200,1394,180,1936]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="FIGURE 4. Gonopodal featUres of Xanthotropis media n. comb. A. Left gonopod, lateral View. B. The same, medial View. C. The same, dorsal View. D. Right gonopod, dorsal View (modified from GoloVatch et al., 2004). Scale lines: A–C (0.5 mm), D (1000 µm)." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/1439778/files/figure.png" pageId="7" pageNumber="358">Fig. 4</figureCitation>
C-D) elongated, curvilinear proximad, indented at midlength then expanding distad with prolonged ventral corner, with retrorse, apically rounded, dorsally lamellate projection arising from medial surface and curving gently dorsad to level of acropodital midlength, extending linearly from origin of dorsal lamella, apically emarginate. Solenomere long, narrow, and acicular, arising at level of cingulum and basally on acropodite, curving broadly laterad away from acropodital stem then sinusoidally along dorsal surface of its distal half, sides narrowing smoothly, apically acuminate and virtually invisible, terminating just beyond lateral acropodital margin at level of retrorse lamella (
<figureCitation box="[159,295,730,755]" captionStart="FIGURE 4" captionStartId="6.[151,250,1949,1971]" captionTargetBox="[207,1386,185,1934]" captionTargetId="figure@6.[200,1394,180,1936]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="FIGURE 4. Gonopodal featUres of Xanthotropis media n. comb. A. Left gonopod, lateral View. B. The same, medial View. C. The same, dorsal View. D. Right gonopod, dorsal View (modified from GoloVatch et al., 2004). Scale lines: A–C (0.5 mm), D (1000 µm)." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/1439778/files/figure.png" pageId="7" pageNumber="358">Figs. 4C–D</figureCitation>
). Spermatic groove arising in pit in prefemir, angling along medial surface of acropodite to base of solenomere, opening apically on latter (
<figureCitation box="[595,686,766,791]" captionStart="FIGURE 4" captionStartId="6.[151,250,1949,1971]" captionTargetBox="[207,1386,185,1934]" captionTargetId="figure@6.[200,1394,180,1936]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="FIGURE 4. Gonopodal featUres of Xanthotropis media n. comb. A. Left gonopod, lateral View. B. The same, medial View. C. The same, dorsal View. D. Right gonopod, dorsal View (modified from GoloVatch et al., 2004). Scale lines: A–C (0.5 mm), D (1000 µm)." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/1439778/files/figure.png" pageId="7" pageNumber="358">Fig. 4D</figureCitation>
). Total length of telopodite 
<quantity box="[997,1086,767,791]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.4" pageId="7" pageNumber="358" unit="mm" value="2.4">2.4 mm</quantity>
. Width of femur in dorsal view 
<quantity box="[151,240,802,827]" metricMagnitude="-4" metricUnit="m" metricValue="5.0" pageId="7" pageNumber="358" unit="mm" value="0.5">0.5 mm</quantity>
.
</paragraph>
